article.headline: McNeese State 31, Sam Houston St. 26
article.story:
LAKE CHARLES, La. (AP) -- Chris Allen returned an interception
for a touchdown and Blake Bercegeay kicked four field goals to help
McNeese State take a 31-26 victory over Sam Houston State on
Saturday.

Mark Fontenot threw for two touchdowns for McNeese (4-2, 2-1
Southland Conference), which took a 21-14 halftime lead after
Fontenot's 9-yard pass to Steve Whitehead with 10 seconds remaining
in the second quarter.

In addition to the costly interception, Sam Houston (2-5, 1-3)
gave up four fumbles, but still got as close as 21-20 after Jason
Godfrey's 2-yard touchdown run with 4:40 left in the third quarter.

Fontenot then connected with Jeremy Haynes on a 21-yard scoring
pass early in the fourth quarter to put the Cowboys back up by
eight. Bercegeay kicked a 45-yard field goal to make it 31-20.

Bercegeay's other kicks were from 25, 20 and 24 yards in the
first half.

Fontenot was 9-of-27 passing for 101 yards and was intercepted
once. Teammate Chris Jones completed 4 of 6 passes for 79 yards.

Sam Houston's Phil Daugherty completed 28 of 45 passes for 261
yards, while Wade Pate was 5-of-6 passing for 60 yards, giving Sam
Houston 321 yards in the air compared to only 19 on the ground.
Daugherty had two touchdown passes and Pate had one. Corey Roberts
caught one TD pass from each quarterback as part of a 10-catch,
112-yard performance.

Kris Bush led McNeese's running game with 76 yards.
